com.hcl.voltmx.middleware.api.events

Class EventData

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.hcl.voltmx.middleware.api.events.EventData

  • public class EventData
extends Object
    EventData class is used to create events with details. These events can be notified to different subscriber depending on the event name or also know as topic. The event name or topic is hierarchical in nature which means it could have child topics as well. Child topics will receive all notifications of parent topic. / is used as separator in topic name. For example, parent topic can be "transaction" and it can have children topics "transaction/credit" and "transaction/debit". Both these child topics will receive all the notifications which are raised on the parent "transaction" topic. However, event raised on child topic "transaction/credit" will be received only by that child.
    Since:
    Foundry V8 SP4 FP2 (8.4.2) release
    See Also:
    EventNotifier, EventManager, EventStatus, EventSubscriber
